<item>
            <title>[SPARK-23614] Union produces incorrect results when caching is used</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-23614</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We just upgraded from 2.2 to 2.3 and our test suite caught this error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;TestData(x: Int, y: Int, z: Int)

val frame = session.createDataset(Seq(TestData(1, 2, 3), TestData(4, 5, 6))).cache()
val group1 = frame.groupBy(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;x&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).agg(min(col(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;y&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)) as &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;value&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
val group2 = frame.groupBy(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;x&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).agg(min(col(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;z&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)) as &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;value&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
group1.union(group2).show()
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// +---+-----+
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// | x|value|
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// +---+-----+
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// | 1| 2|
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// | 4| 5|
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// | 1| 2|
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// | 4| 5|
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// +---+-----+
&lt;/span&gt;group2.union(group1).show()
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// +---+-----+
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// | x|value|
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// +---+-----+
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// | 1| 3|
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// | 4| 6|
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// | 1| 3|
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// | 4| 6|
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// +---+-----+&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The error disappears if the first data frame is not cached or if the two group by&apos;s use separate copies. I&apos;m not sure exactly what happens on the insides of Spark, but errors that produce incorrect results rather than exceptions always concerns me.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
